The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control Wednesday night confirmed 22 new cases of coronavirus. 15 of the new cases were confirmed in Lagos, 4 in Nigeria’s capital city Abuja, 2 in Bauchi State and 1 in Edo State,” NCDC said. “As at 09:00pm 8th April there are 276 confirmed cases of #COVID19 reported in Nigeria. Forty-four have been discharged with six deaths,” it added. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .